<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="SC3" checkit-title="Venn Diagrams">
    <statement>
        <p>
            A survey asks 400 people the following question: "Do you prefer beer or wine?" In their answer, the respondents can specify one of the two options, both, or neither. Suppose 156 reported that they prefer beer only, 212 reported that they prefer beer, 145 reported that they prefer neither beer nor wine, and 43 reported that they prefer wine only.
            <ol>
                <li>Draw a Venn diagram of the situation. Use the information in the problem to clearly label the diagram.</li>
                <li>How many people  reported that they prefer wine?</li>
                <li>How many people  reported that they do not prefer wine?</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>In general you should draw overlapping circles contained in a larger rectangle. From the information given in this problem, 400 is the amount for the entire rectangle, 156 is the number for the crescent moon part of beer, 212 is the number for the entire beer circle, 145 is the number for the portion outside of both circles, and 43 is the number for the crescent moon part of wine.</li>
                <li>99 reported that they prefer wine.</li>
                <li>301 reported that they do not prefer wine.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
